title: friendly lambdas and higher-order programming
pid: 4f746f16-da5b-4d81-88d1-00403d886de4
body: |2-
    Lambda expressions and higher-order programming are much friendlier in Haskell. Compare:

  ``` python
  def f (x,y,z ):
    return 2x + 3y / z

  g = lambda z: f(1,2,z)
  ```

  ``` haskell
  f x y z = 2x + 3y / z

  g = \z -> f 1 2 z
  ```

  Or equivalently and even easier to read:
  ``` haskell
  f x y z = 2x + 3y / z

  g = f 1 2
  ```
